This project performs sentiment analysis on Twitter data to classify tweets as positive, negative, or neutral. It uses natural language processing (NLP) techniques to understand public opinion around a topic, brand, or event.

üìÅ Dataset

The dataset contains tweets collected from Twitter using keywords or hashtags.
Each tweet includes:

Text
Label (Positive / Negative / Neutral)

Objectives

Preprocess raw tweet text (remove hashtags, links, punctuation, etc.)
Tokenize and vectorize the text
Train a sentiment classifier
Evaluate the model and visualize sentiment distribution
 Tools & Libraries

Python
Pandas, NumPy
NLTK  (for preprocessing )
Scikit-learn (for training classifiers)
Matplotlib / Seaborn 
Jupyter Notebook

